parameters:
Umi vanished from this world due to the power of curse magic, so there's no
remains here...
There are only the letters carved into the stone...
Yet, I've come to this place many times, thinking of Umi.
Her fiery red hair, her lustrous skin, her rich laughter...

All of it was dear to me, but time cruelly stole the fine details from my
memory.

Gradually, the image I remembered became more abstract, and with each
change, the void of loneliness expanded.

Peace has come... It's an irreplaceable treasure... There's no doubt about
that...
But in that calmness, like a lull, I just wept...
I just... wanted to see Umi...

As the village was being rebuilt and everyone's expressions brightened, I
left the village...
I couldn't stay in this village anymore... That's what I thought.
It's not anyone's fault... Everyone welcomed me warmly and healed together.
But... I had reached my limit...

I don't know if there's salvation at the end of this aimless journey, but I
think I'll walk on.
If forgetting is to be healed, then I don't need such a thing...
I'll live on, embracing the loneliness and nourishing myself with memories.
In the world that Umi protected...
